33:22.170 --> 33:23.376
AH! IT'S MINE!
OKAY, GO!

33:23.480 --> 33:26.688
- WE NEED
TO MAKE SOMETHING EXCITING,

33:26.790 --> 33:28.098
BECAUSE--
- [laughing]

33:28.210 --> 33:30.371
IT'S THE HIGHEST CARD WINS.
[grunts]

33:30.490 --> 33:31.240
- THERE'S NO STRATEGY
TO THIS GAME.

33:31.350 --> 33:32.419
WHOEVER INVENTED THIS GAME--

33:32.520 --> 33:34.488
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
THERE'S NO STRATEGY?

33:34.590 --> 33:35.522
IT'S--YOU--

33:35.630 --> 33:36.904
- THE PERSON WHO INVENTED
THE GAME,

33:37.010 --> 33:38.693
HE HAD A SHORT DAY THAT DAY.
- [laughing]

33:38.800 --> 33:39.835
HE JUST CAME IN AND SAID,

33:39.940 --> 33:41.043
"ALL RIGHT,
WE NEED ANOTHER GAME."

33:41.150 --> 33:43.015
- SEVEN BEATS SIX!
- I DON'T EVEN...

33:43.120 --> 33:44.280
- IT'S A CLASSIC!
IT'S A CLASSIC.

33:44.400 --> 33:46.607
- LET'S JUST DRINK SOME MORE.
HOW ABOUT THAT?

33:46.710 --> 33:47.916
- OH, MAN!

33:48.020 --> 33:49.817
- A LITTLE MORE.

33:49.920 --> 33:51.364
- WHAT DO YOU GOT GOING ON HERE?
CAN I SEE THESE FOR A SECOND?

33:51.470 --> 33:54.507
LET ME SEE.
- WHY? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

33:54.610 --> 33:55.713
OH, THIS IS NOT GOOD.

33:55.820 --> 33:57.378
THIS IS GONNA BE--
THIS IS GONNA END UP HORRIBLE.

33:59.030 --> 34:00.406
- I CAN'T--
I DON'T SEE ANYTHING NOW.

34:00.520 --> 34:03.409
IS THIS YOUR GLASS?
- OH, WOW. WOW!

34:03.520 --> 34:05.863
YOU KNOW WHAT?
- I CAN'T SEE.

34:05.970 --> 34:08.131
I CAN HEAR YOU.
THAT'S ALL.

34:08.250 --> 34:10.389
THAT'S ONE THING.
I WILL NEVER LOSE YOU.

34:10.490 --> 34:11.479
'CAUSE...

34:11.600 --> 34:13.249
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'LL NEVER LOSE ME?

34:13.360 --> 34:14.759
- WELL, BECAUSE I COULD ALWAYS
FOLLOW THE SOUND.

34:14.880 --> 34:16.939
- HMM.

34:17.050 --> 34:19.018
- LIKE I DON'T LIKE LISTENING
TO PEOPLE.

34:19.120 --> 34:20.496
I ALSO DON'T LIKE
LOOKING AT PEOPLE

34:20.610 --> 34:21.599
- HMM.

34:21.710 --> 34:23.496
- I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'VE NOTICED THAT.

34:23.610 --> 34:24.747
- I HAVE.

34:24.850 --> 34:27.956
- EYE CONTACT IS NOT
ONE OF MY FAVORITE THINGS.

34:28.060 --> 34:31.336
YET WITH YOU...

34:31.440 --> 34:35.206
I FIND IT HARD
NOT TO LOOK IN YOUR EYES.

34:56.050 --> 34:57.677
WHAT ARE YOU DOING SATURDAY?

34:59.820 --> 35:02.709
[rock music]

35:04.720 --> 35:07.188
- [talking under breath]

35:07.310 --> 35:11.406
- BABY, I DON'T KNOW

35:11.520 --> 35:14.102
- YOU WANT
SOME OF THIS BODY TONIC?

35:14.210 --> 35:16.132
- OKAY.
- YEAH, IT SAYS IT, UH...

35:16.250 --> 35:19.697
CLEANSES AND ENERGIZES.

35:19.800 --> 35:22.689
- THAT'S GOOD.
- AND I'M FEELING ENERGIZED.

35:22.810 --> 35:23.799
- ALL RIGHT!
- ALL RIGHT.

35:23.910 --> 35:25.662
YOU READY FOR THIS?
- YEAH.

35:25.770 --> 35:29.080
- THINK YOU CAN LOCATE
THE JOHNSON FILE?

35:29.190 --> 35:32.466
- HONEY, YOU LOOK SO AWESOME.
WOW.

35:32.570 --> 35:35.983
- YOU WANTED THIS JOB.
- I LIKE IT.

35:36.090 --> 35:37.261
- ARE YOU OKAY?
- SEXY. YEAH.

35:37.370 --> 35:39.543
I'M READY TO GO
TO FUNKYTOWN.

35:39.650 --> 35:41.379
- HONEY, YOU DON'T LOOK GOOD.

35:41.480 --> 35:44.278
WHAT IS IT?
- [sighs]

35:45.480 --> 35:46.856
- OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

35:46.970 --> 35:48.369
- I'M SO SORRY. NO, I SUCK.
- LET'S JUST GET YOU TO BED.

35:48.490 --> 35:51.891
- I SUCK SO BAD.
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.

35:52.010 --> 35:53.272
- I JUST--
- IT'S OKAY.

35:53.390 --> 35:55.529
- I HIT A WALL.
I REALLY DID.

35:55.630 --> 35:57.211
I WAS READY TO GO
LIKE SIX MINUTES AGO,

35:57.320 --> 35:59.049
AND THEN I JUST HIT A WALL.

35:59.150 --> 36:00.071
- YOU FEEL SICK?
- NO, I DON'T FEEL SICK.

36:00.190 --> 36:02.841
I JUST--
- ALL RIGHT.

36:02.950 --> 36:04.258
- I'M JUST SO TIRED.
- OKAY.

36:04.360 --> 36:06.294
HERE'S WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO.
- WHAT?

36:06.400 --> 36:08.015
- GET YOU SOME WATER.
- NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

36:08.130 --> 36:09.358
DON'T DO THIS.
IT'S LIKE $12 A BOTTLE.

36:09.470 --> 36:11.119
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

36:11.230 --> 36:12.436
HERE YOU GO.
- YOU'RE AWESOME.

36:12.540 --> 36:13.746
- BEFORE YOU GO TO BED,
HAVE SOME WATER.

36:13.860 --> 36:15.953
- HONEY, YOU'RE SO AWESOME.

36:16.070 --> 36:18.265
I'M SORRY.
I'M SUCH A TEASE.

36:20.410 --> 36:22.970
I'M SORRY, BABE.
- IT'S OKAY.

36:23.070 --> 36:24.241
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
- YOU GOT ALL OILED UP AND...

36:24.350 --> 36:26.454
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

36:26.560 --> 36:28.039
- YOU HAVE ON
YOUR MERV GRIFFIN JACKET.

36:28.150 --> 36:28.969
- IT'S FINE.
I PROMISE, OKAY?

36:29.080 --> 36:31.139
[phone chimes]

36:31.250 --> 36:32.148
- HONEY, CAN YOU GET THAT,
PLEASE?

36:32.250 --> 36:33.217
- JUST IGNORE IT.
- NO, PLEASE.

36:33.320 --> 36:34.389
- IGNORE IT.
- I'LL SLEEP BETTER.

36:34.500 --> 36:35.592
- JUST RELAX, OKAY?
I'LL GET IT.

36:35.710 --> 36:36.495
JUST YOU RELAX.
- I KNOW, I'M RELAXED.

36:36.600 --> 36:40.115
I'M RELAXED.
I'M RELAXED.

36:40.230 --> 36:41.390
WHO WAS IT?

36:41.500 --> 36:45.288
- IT'S FROM AMBER.

36:46.370 --> 36:47.883
- AW.
[Amber laughter]

36:47.990 --> 36:48.922
- REALLY GOOD.
- BYE.

36:49.030 --> 36:50.372
- BYE.
- ALL RIGHT, YOU KIDS.

36:50.480 --> 36:51.128
[both laughing]

36:51.240 --> 36:52.719
- YOU GUYS HAVE FUN!

36:52.830 --> 36:55.060
- THAT'S REALLY SWEET.
- NOT TOO MUCH FUN.

36:55.170 --> 36:57.798
- YOU'RE SOMETHING ELSE,
YOU KNOW THAT?

36:57.900 --> 37:00.551
- THAT WIG IS HIDEOUS.
I GOTTA GET RID OF THIS WIG.

37:00.660 --> 37:03.037
WHAT WAS I THINKING?
- I LIKE IT.

37:03.150 --> 37:05.141
- IT'S AWFUL!
- YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL.

37:05.250 --> 37:07.832
- YOU'RE NICE.

37:07.940 --> 37:09.146
- WHOO!
- WHOO!

37:09.260 --> 37:10.659
- OW!
- START IT!

37:10.780 --> 37:11.804
- PLAY IT AGAIN.

37:25.340 --> 37:26.784
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- WHAT ARE YOUDOING?

37:26.890 --> 37:30.929
I WOKE UP, AND YOU WERE GONE.
- GOING? LEAVING?

37:31.040 --> 37:33.031
- I THOUGHT--I THOUGHT
YOU WERE FEELING WEIRD,

37:33.140 --> 37:34.789
AND YOU WANTED ME TO GO.

37:34.900 --> 37:38.381
- NO WEIRDER THAN EVER, REALLY.
- OH.

37:38.490 --> 37:40.526
- FIGURED YOU'RE LIKE A TEN-HOUR
A NIGHT PERSON.

37:40.630 --> 37:42.769
- WELL, I FIGURED
YOU WERE LIKE

37:42.880 --> 37:45.280
HAVING SOME, YOU KNOW,
"YOU" TIME SOMEWHERE.

37:45.400 --> 37:48.847
- NO, I WAS GOING TO LOUISA'S.
LOUISA'S--

37:48.950 --> 37:50.292
THEY HAVE THESE CROISSANTS.
YOU GOTTA GET THERE AT 7:00.

37:50.400 --> 37:53.608
AND YOU GOTTA TASTE THESE.

37:53.710 --> 37:57.407
THESE ARE UNBELIEVABLE.
- OKAY.

37:57.510 --> 37:58.954
- YOU'RE STAYING, RIGHT?
- YEAH, I'M STAYING.

37:59.060 --> 38:00.231
- ALL RIGHT, SO HERE.
TRY THIS.

38:00.340 --> 38:03.753
OH, DON'T TOUCH IT YET.

38:03.860 --> 38:06.920
SOME PEOPLE LIKE TO, UH--
YOU CAN HAVE THE COFFEE--

38:07.040 --> 38:08.894
PUT JELLY ON IT.

38:09.010 --> 38:10.238
AND THOSE PEOPLE,

38:10.350 --> 38:12.102
THEY SHOULD BE SLAPPED
AND ARRESTED.

38:12.220 --> 38:14.620
'CAUSE THE WAY TO DO IT
IS A LITTLE MELTED BUTTER.

38:14.740 --> 38:16.879
I SWEAR TO GOD.
- [laughing]

38:16.980 --> 38:20.017
- 'CAUSE THIS IS JUST WARM
ENOUGH TO KINDA MELT IT.

38:20.120 --> 38:23.772
- SO YOU GOT UP, UH, EARLY
AND...

38:23.880 --> 38:24.983
GOT SOME TREATS.

38:25.090 --> 38:28.298
YOU WERE GONNA SURPRISE ME
IN BED, WEREN'T YOU?

38:30.820 --> 38:33.857
- I DON'T THINK
THAT'S ANY OF YOUR BUSINESS

38:33.960 --> 38:34.198
WHAT I WAS GONNA DO.

38:34.310 --> 38:37.928
- I SEE.

38:38.030 --> 38:39.850
- JUST TASTE IT.

38:42.900 --> 38:43.867
RIGHT?
- MM!

38:43.970 --> 38:46.837
MM! SO WARM!
- YEAH.

38:46.940 --> 38:49.556
ALL RIGHT, NOW GET OUT.

38:49.670 --> 38:51.877
- COME ON, VICTOR, BUDDY.
WE GOTTA GO.

38:51.980 --> 38:54.778
WE'RE GONNA BE LATE.
- I'M STILL GETTING READY.

38:54.880 --> 38:56.086
- YOU'RE GETTING--
WELL, LET ME HELP YOU.

38:56.190 --> 39:00.058
HERE, LET ME--

39:00.160 --> 39:03.641
VICTOR, WHY IS THE DOOR LOCKED?
- I WANT JOEL TO TAKE ME.

39:03.750 --> 39:09.029
- OKAY, WELL, JOEL HAS GONE TO
WORK EARLY THIS MORNING ALREADY.

39:09.130 --> 39:11.337
SO...

39:11.450 --> 39:14.658
I GOTTA TAKE YOU.
BUT IT'S TIME TO GO, OKAY?

39:14.760 --> 39:18.480
VICTOR, CAN YOU OPEN THE DOOR,
PLEASE?

39:21.910 --> 39:25.528
HEY, LISTEN, I KNOW YOU'RE
UPSET ABOUT YESTERDAY.

39:28.460 --> 39:31.349
BUT IT'S TIME TO GO TO SCHOOL,
ALL RIGHT?

39:31.470 --> 39:35.122
SO...

39:35.230 --> 39:39.405
CAN YOU TALK TO ME?

39:39.510 --> 39:41.740
VICTOR?

39:44.270 --> 39:48.855
VICTOR?

39:52.730 --> 39:54.891
- FOR REAL?
- WHAT?

39:55.010 --> 39:56.238
- YOU'RE GONNA EAT THIS?

39:56.350 --> 39:57.863
- YEAH!
IT'S SQUISHY.

39:57.980 --> 39:59.698
- ALL RIGHT, I'LL BELIEVE IT
WHEN I SEE IT.

39:59.810 --> 40:00.629
LAST TIME YOU TOOK
A TANGERINE TO SCHOOL,

40:00.740 --> 40:04.153
IT CAME BACK--
- WE'RE HOME!

40:04.260 --> 40:05.534
- GRANDMA!

40:05.640 --> 40:08.359
- THERE HE IS!

40:08.470 --> 40:11.291
- OKAY.
- CAN YOU TAKE ME TO SCHOOL?

40:11.400 --> 40:12.776
- SLOW DOWN, SWEETIE.
SHE JUST GOT HERE.

40:12.890 --> 40:13.675
HEY.
- HEY.

40:13.790 --> 40:16.122
UH, YOU NEED HELP
WITH THE BAGS?

40:16.240 --> 40:17.264
- NO, NO, NO.
WE GOT IT.

40:17.380 --> 40:19.234
UM, JABBAR,
GET YOUR GRANDMA'S BAG.

40:19.340 --> 40:20.648
- OKAY.
- THANK YOU.

40:20.760 --> 40:24.412
- THIS IS HEAW.
- GOOD MORNING.

40:24.520 --> 40:27.489
- WELCOME.

40:27.590 --> 40:30.866
- I'M SORRY ABOUT THIS,
CROSBY.

40:31.730 --> 40:34.597
- [sighs]
SORRY ABOUT WHAT?

40:34.700 --> 40:37.567
- COME ON.
I KNOW THAT I'M PUTTING YOU OUT.

40:37.670 --> 40:38.773
AND I HATE IT.

40:38.880 --> 40:42.259
BUT IT WON'T BE FOR LONG.
I PROMISE.

40:42.370 --> 40:46.534
AT ANY RATE,
THE POINT IS THANK YOU.

40:46.650 --> 40:49.710
I APPRECIATE IT.
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN.

40:55.930 --> 40:59.889
- I'M SPORADICALLY A GOOD MAN,
BUT, UM--

41:00.000 --> 41:03.584
THANK YOU AND, UM, YOU KNOW,
YOU DON'T NEED TO BE SORRY.

41:03.700 --> 41:05.008
WE'RE--WE'RE VERY HAPPY
TO HAVE YOU.

41:05.110 --> 41:10.116
UM, ESPECIALLY JABBAR.
HE'S THROUGH THE ROOF.

41:10.220 --> 41:12.040
SO MI CASA, SU CASA.

41:12.150 --> 41:15.870
WELCOME, AND I'M HAPPY
YOU'RE HERE TOO.

41:15.990 --> 41:20.017
- THANK YOU.
- YOU STAY AS LONG AS YOU WANT.

41:20.130 --> 41:22.473
- WELL, WE WON'T GO THAT FAR.
- OKAY.

41:22.580 --> 41:24.263
LET ME SHOW YOU
WHAT WE DID WITH THE OLD LAIR.

41:24.370 --> 41:27.954
LOTS OF CHANGES.
- OH, MY!

41:28.070 --> 41:30.755
LOOK AT THIS!

41:30.860 --> 41:32.794
- PUT IN A NEW CEILING FAN
FOR YOU.

41:32.900 --> 41:34.993
I HEARD THAT YOU LIKE IT
WINDY AND NOISY.

41:35.110 --> 41:37.999
[gentle pop music]
